The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 16 February is 218,557 (25,190 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 11 February, there were 7,969 new confirmed cases (918.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 04 February, there were 10,264 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 22% (2,295 fewer cases).
